Development Investment Bank (DLM) Capital Group on Thursday announced the launch of its digital bank – Sof­ri, its one-stop-shop mobile app alongside the unveiling of Sof­ri’s Brand Ambassador, Sam­uel Perry (aka) BrodaShaggi. Sofri derives its brand name from the Pidgin En­glish expression “sofrisofri” which translates to “easy” or “stress-free”. Sofri digital bank identifies with the fi­nancial hassles of everyday living and portrays an easy access to providing solutions to these problems. The digital bank, available on both Android and IOS stores, is designed as a one-stop-shop approach to all its users and will include loans, investments and savings products. Funsho Idowu, MD/CEO of Sofri, while speaking to the press at the launch, said: “The Sofri app is designed to strengthen our commitment to our clients and provide them with access to renewed solutions, especially in to­day’s digital world”.